More than 2,500 dogs representing 138 breeds, will compete for prizes at Sunday's All 
Breed Dog Show and Obedience Trials at the Los Angeles Sports Arena.   Between 
judgings, a troupe of Dobermans will jump through hoops and barrels and will scale 
walls.  In the scent relay, teams of dogs will jump over hurdles and locate the jackets of 
their owners.  There will also be a demonstration of how dogs herd farm animals.   There 
will also be an expert to answer questions on behavioral questions about dogs, free 
veterinary advice, and a computer for visitors to learn which breed would best suit their 
life style.</SUM>

